    Casper de Clercq | Norwest Venture Partners | ZoomInfo.com

Casper L. de Clercq: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 29, 2017 4:57 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Norwest Venture Partners



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Casper L. de Clercq  General Partner, Norwest Venture PartnersAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 10 different industries.See Board Relationships53--
Background

		Mr. Casper L. de Clercq serves as the Head of Healthcare Investing and General Partner of Norwest Venture Partners. Mr. de Clercq has over 30 years of experience, having led marketing and commercialization efforts for companies that span the healthcare space. He has extensive operating experience, having led marketing and commercialization efforts for cardiovascular device, specialty pharmaceutical and diagnostic companies. He served as a Partner at Norwest Venture Partners ... since January 2011. He focuses on mid and late stage investments in consumer and digital health, healthcare IT, medical devices and diagnostics, technology-enabled healthcare services and specialty pharmaceuticals. He was a Venture Partner and Partner at U.S. Venture Partners. He joined U.S. Venture Partners in 2004 and invested in therapeutic companies from clinical development through commercialization. Over the six year period, he was actively involved in making and managing investments in more than a dozen companies as a member of the healthcare team. Prior to 2004, he was heavily involved in several rounds of financing and the initial public offering process at Aerogen, Inc., where he served as Vice President of Sales & Marketing since 1999 and Vice President of Business Development from 1998 to 2000. He spent four years as a Vice President of Business Development, Sales & Marketing at the firm. In 1999, he co-founded and Venture Funded Epicor to develop a market leading epicardial ablation treatment for atrial fibrillation. He held senior sales and marketing positions with Heartport and served as its Director of Market Development from 1996 to 1998. At the firm, he launched an integrated surgical product line to perform minimally invasive cardiovascular surgery. He also held various senior marketing positions at Diagnostic Products Corporation from 1987 to 1991. At these companies, he worked closely with the engineering, scientific and clinical teams in product development, coordinated multiple U.S. product launches and had ongoing responsibility for managing international distribution. He co-founded Biointerventions Co. and served as its Vice President of Business Development from 1994 to 1995. He served as a Strategy Consultant at Bain & Company from 1984 to 1987. He has been a Director of Crossover Health, Inc. since January 27, 2015. He has been Independent Director of Telcare, Inc. since October 23, 2014. He serves as a Director at NextHealth Technologies Inc., Misfit Wearables and Simpirica Spine, Inc. He has been a Director at Science Exchange, Inc. since June 2017. He served as a Director of AtheroMed, Inc, Ilypsa, Inc. and Valeritas Holdings, Inc. (Also known as Valeritas, Inc.). He served as a Director of Basis Science, Inc. He served as a Director of Intersect ENT, Inc. from February 2013 to June 4, 2015. He served as a Director of Volcano AtheroMed, Inc. He served as an Independent Director of iRhythm Technologies, Inc. from March 2013 to June 14, 2017. He served as a Private Investor and Board Member of Innospine. Mr. de Clercq holds an MBA from Stanford University Graduate School of Business, an M.Sc. in Biological Science from Stanford University, an M.A. in Biology and Immunology from Stanford University and a B.A. in Biochemistry from Dartmouth College.Read Full Background




