Casper L. de Clercq, MBA

Age : 53Linked companies : No connection available 





Summary 



Mr. Casper L. de Clercq is General Partner at Norwest Venture Partners and Limited Partner at Mammoth Equity Partners LLC.He currently serves on the boards of iRhythm Technologies, Telcare, and Crossover Health.Prior to joining NVP, Mr. de Clercq was a Partner at U.S. Venture Partners in Menlo Park, where he invested in therapeutic companies from clinical development through commercialization. At USVP, he served as a Board member for AtheroMed, Ilypsa and Valeritas. Previously, he spent four years as Vice President of Business Development, Sales and Marketing at Aerogen, a specialty pharmaceutical company developing inhaled therapeutics for diabetes and respiratory diseases. In 1999 he co-founded and venture funded Epicor to develop a market leading epicardial ablation treatment for atrial fibrillation. Before Epicor, Mr. de Clercq held senior marketing positions at Heartport and Diagnostic Products Corp. At Heartport, he launched an integrated surgical product line to perform minimally invasive cardiovascular surgery. Previously at Diagnostics Products Corp., he managed a portfolio of oncology, infectious disease and infertility immunoassay tests which doubled to $105M in revenues during his tenure. At these companies, Mr. de Clercq worked closely with the engineering, scientific and clinical teams in product development, coordinated multiple U.S. product launches and had ongoing responsibility for managing international distribution. Earlier in his career, he worked internationally for three years as a strategy consultant for Bain & Co. Mr. de Clercq was previously employed as Venture Partner by Presidio Management Group.He also served on the board at AtheroMed, Inc., Ilypsa, Inc., and Valeritas, Inc.Mr. de Clercq holds an M.B.A. from Stanford University Graduate School of Business, an M.S. in biological science from Stanford University and a B.A. in biochemistry from Dartmouth College.



Holdings of Casper L. de Clercq, MBA 










